args:
Nevin's team infiltrates Rozcimea to gather intel
on the demonic incidents, but no sooner do they
find a lead than Basileus appears with demonic
entities in tow. Just as all hope seems lost for
the apostles, Harle comes to their aid.
Welcome back, Little Pi! Are you all right?\nNo run-ins with creepy strangers?
I'm not a child, Gabrielâ€”you don't have to\nworry about me every time I go outside.
More importantly, I tracked down the\nlocation of the journal we're after.
You heard her, Nevin. What's the plan?
The South Grastaea wroth incident...\nThe memory manipulation in Paradise...\nThe revival of the Five Archdemons...

Though each case was more or less resolved,
a host of questions remainedâ€”so Ramiel, Pinon, 
Gabriel, and I started digging through Church
documents for any information on demons that
might help shed some light on things.
Sadly, the only thing we learned was that the\nChurch's records concerning demons are scant.\nUnnaturally so.
Take the Empyrean War fought centuries ago by\nangels and demons. The Church was up to its\neyeballs in that, yet no real records remain.
Interestingly, documents aren't the only thing\nmissing when it comes to that conflict...
The Empyrean War? Well, after driving\nback the demons, I know Metatron... Hmm.\nApologies, but my memory is a bit hazy.
I'd been with Ramiel long enough to know he\nwasn't lying, but there's no way he'd ever forget\nsomething like that without a bit of ï¼‚assistance.ï¼‚
There was only one explanation that made sense:\nSomebody was manipulating both the records and\nthe angels' memories. But whoâ€”and why?
Either way, it meant digging through archives was\na waste of time, so we decided to take our search\noutside the Church.
I figured there had to be intact records\nout there somewhere.

But just as I came to that conclusion, Sandalphon
showed up and told me to start with the previous
Wing of Purityâ€”Pinon's motherâ€”and look into the
last mission she took on.

She'd been tasked with retrieving a sealing stone
stolen by a military-run state. The perp tried to use
it to revive a demon, just like during the wroth
incident. And while Pinon's mom manged to stop
them, it came at the cost of her life.
Of course, the official Church record basically\nmade no mention of the demon, but what about\nrecords kept by the other side?

At the very least, it seemed obvious that whoever
stole the stone knew something about demons,
which meant they also might have left a trail of
breadcrumbs for me to follow.

Anyway, I followed those leads here and there,
and eventually learned that the perp kept a
journal that was chock-full of juicy info about
both the incident and demons.
If we want to learn anything useful, we need that\njournalâ€”and I'll do whatever it takes to get it.
All right, time to stop spacing out.\nWe're nearly there.
I was deep in thought! \nSo, are you really sure about this?
This again? Look, I appreciate you being\nsensitive about my mother's death.\nI really do.
But all of that happened before I was old\nenough to know about it. In truth, I don't\neven remember her.
The only mother I've ever known is Gabriel.
Aw, Piii! Can I give you a hug?\nI'm giving you a hug.
Not while we're on a mission, thank you.
If she says it's not a problem, it's not.\nNow let's get going before we drag this\nout any longer and the sun comes up.
Fair enough. Let's do this thing.\nI am the apostle Nevin, one hand\nof etcetera etceteraâ€”

Hey, you can't leave out the Goddess part!
Also, you're actually making it LONGER!
Ugh. Never mind. I am the apostle Pinon,
one hand of the Goddess!
The vault's secure. Nothing to report.
Understood. I'll take watch from here.\nReturn to your standby location.
All right, let's get ourselves inside.
That took a lot longer than I'd hoped.\nSecurity's surprisingly tight around here.
We've got less than a half hour before the\nnext shift change, so we need to find that\njournal right now.
Satan?! That's what Basileus was after!
Anything useful about Satan's resurrection\nwritten in there?
Right, okay. This says the Five Archdemons\nwere originally derived from Satan and\nhold fragments of his flesh inside them.
Those fragments need a vessel to serve\nas their heart and drive them, so... Oh,\nhang on. There's a note in the margin.
ï¼‚Flesh and heart alone may not suffice.\nWhat about the soul? Further investigation\nis required.ï¼‚

Wish that last part made more sense,
but at least we've got some intel on
Satan's revival now. Ramiel, you'd better
report this back to Sandalphon.
...I can't! Some kind of barrier is cutting\noff my link to her!
Just like what happened in Paradise.\nSo does that meanâ€”
The timing of that barrier and the blast\nline up too well to be a coincidence.\nPapa Bear smells a trap.
We need to get out of here. Now!
See how they bear our form? These are\nclearly the same demonic entities we\nfought previously.
Such numbers... Just how many people\ndid they expose to the miasma?!
Necessary sacrifices to protect this world,\nI'm afraid.
Should have known I'd find you slinking\naround this business, Basileus!
I had faith you would all arrive here.
Well, can't say I approve of your taste\nin welcoming parties.
How could you do such a thing?!
Actually, it was your meddling in my plans\nthat forced my hand.
Your plan to revive Satan, you mean.
Yes. Once the sealed archdemons were all\nreleased from their mimicries, my plan\nentered its final phase.

They have been sharpening their claws in
preparation for this day, and now only
Satan's return remains to be completed.
You cannot stop me.
There are a host of conditions for bringing\nback Satan. Are you truly claiming to have\nalready met them all?
I see you read the journal. In that case,\nallow me to tell you a fun little fact...
The vessel required for Satan's revival...\nis me.
The hell's that supposed to mean?
Precisely what it sounds like, Nevin:\nI will become a part of himâ€”\nI will become his heart.
Are you mad?! You'll never survive that,\neven with your strength!
And what of it? Salvation for the world at\nthe cost of a single life? I can imagine no\ngreater bargain.
How can you talk about salvation for the\nworld after bringing about this massacre?!
Because it prevented a far greater tragedy.\nIf the deaths of a few ensure the survival\nof the many, it is immoral not to do so.
Don't you dare speak to me of morality!\nSalvation bought with blood is no true\nsalvation at all!
Oh, my sweet, naive Pinon... Your words\nonly serve to demonstrate what a\nprivileged upbringing you enjoyed.
Just what do you mean by that?!
I have nothing further to say.
I'm afraid we aren't done speaking until\nyou answer all of our questions. ...Nevin!
Sorry, Basileus, but we're in a bit of a\nhurry and I need to end this!
Is that flattery I hear? I'm touched!
Not flatteryâ€”a sincere estimation of your\nskill. Clearly I was right to have made\npreparations.
Can't...feel my connection to Pinon...\nthrough the Sigil!
You see, this little device of mine saps\nangelic force and severs the Sigil bond.\nI'm afraid yours is now dormant.
Again, you are naive. More often than not,\nhonor is but a cause of deathâ€”and the\ndead can protect nothing.
And you still call in the demonic entities?\nYou're a real piece of work, you know that?
Judging by your expression, I'd say you've\nhad contact with the fake me.

Then you're the true Harle? Well, well.
This is certainly unexpected. But seeing
as the situation has changed, I see no
reason to loiter here any further.
Oh, but this is the perfect chance for us\nto get to know each other!
My task here is complete. Apologies,\nbut I have no interest in knowing you.
My friends here will be a pale substitute,\nbut you can deal with them instead.\nDo try not to die now.

Well, that leaves me with little choice.
And you lot there! Are you going to stand
around sucking wind, or do you want to
be useful?
Chatty little fellow, isn't he...? Still,\nol' Papa Bear can't just sit around\nafter being called out like that!
How lovely to hear! In that case, let's\ncelebrate our newfound friendship with\nsome commemorative violence!
